Confluence could have the possibility of a "black list" of file names and all files names located in that list wouldn't be searchable in the interface even if the user places the exact file name in the search field.

Confluence also could have an option to remove files like JPG, PNG, or other files types from the index.

h4. Step to reproduce
# Create a page
# Attach a wide Excel spreadsheet to Confluence page or simply download this [^A_Very_Wide_Spreadsheet.xls]
# Add [view file macro|https://confluence.atlassian.com/x/mIkpCg] to the attached Excel file in the page
# Export the page to PDF
# You will notice that the table gets truncated [^truncated_PDFexport.pdf]

h4. Workaround
Add the following CSS in the [PDF stylesheet|https://confluence.atlassian.com/x/MYJaCw#CustomisingExportstoPDF-CustomisingthePDFStylesheet]:
{code}
.office-document table
{
   table-layout: auto !important;
   width: auto !important;
}
{code} 
You can see the result like this now after applying the above CSS - [^better_PDFexport.pdf]

